52.7	Iconoclasm	Iconoclasm	Iconoclasm is the deliberate destruction of religious icons and other symbols or monuments, usually with religious or political motives. It is a frequent component of major political or religious changes. The term encompasses the more specific destruction of images of a ruler after his death or overthrow , for example, following Akhenaten's death in Ancient Egypt.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/2008-09_Nijmegen_st_stevens_beeldenstorm.JPG/330px-2008-09_Nijmegen_st_stevens_beeldenstorm.JPG
